        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> 20 - 30kpp is a bit extreme, especially if you already have high tradeskills from working on the shawl or ring quests.</P><P>With access to the right individuals and the willingness to trade out combines on items so others do combines for you, it won't cost you more than 5kpp. I'm currently doing the quest with two guildmates and we're down to finishing the robe and finishing the sickle. We've spent a total of 9kpp so far (3kpp of that was for 3 steins and most of the rest was on the previous 15 sickle attempts before we found a 240+ smith). We expect to spend about another 3kpp (at most) before its finished. So all told, 12kpp/3 means 4kpp for 5 AC/STR/STA, 8 INT/WIS, 55HP/Mana, FT1.</P><P>This quest is a hell of a lot of work, but like the shawl and the ring quests, it is (at times) fun and some of the resulting items by themselves are really nice. Give it a go, but expect to invest several days and quite a bit of plat.</P><P></P><P><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=11316" target="_blank">Vaemas Samedi</a><BR>Warlock of Veeshan<BR>Member, Cestus Dei<BR>Keeper of Chester the Warduck</font></td>
